TopicTitle: KSP won't start on Steam, Ubuntu 16.04

Articles.Content:
Hello,

Before anybody asks: I've spent a lot of time reading through the linux support thread found here: 

I've also spent hours "Googling" over the course of the last week. I have tried many different suggestions and I simply cannot find one that works.

My issue:

When I try to launch KSP from steam it shows a small black window loading the game. That window vanishes and nothing happens. I also can't launch it directly from the terminal.

Things I have tried:

  • LC_ALL=C and %command%=_64
  • sudo apt-get update and upgrade
  • Installing 32 bit stuff
  • Changing "SteamApps" to "steamapps"
  • Changing the graphics driver (it's nvidia, I tried old, new, and default)
  • Uninstall/reinstall multiple times - to include deleting all leftover files manually
  • Various other fixes found online
  • Opening the game inside or outside of Steam
  • Making sure the pertinent files are executable

If I run ./KSP.x86_64 (with or without the "LC_ALL=C") I get the error "There is no data folder". For the life of me I cannot find out what is causing this to happen. I know there is a Unity compatibility issue with KSP launching but I'm not able to find enough on how to get around it other than the fact that the issue exists. I have found that there could be a problem with the capital/lowercase reading of folder names. Again, nothing that points to what it -should- be set to in order to work.

If I run the launcher, the launcher will show up but when I hit "play" the launcher will vanish and the game will fail to launch. I've tried deleting, renaming, and everything with any of the data folders and it just doesn't work. I'm at the point where I am exhausted from trying. I'm about to throw in the towel on KSP. I really hope somebody has some insight to offer!

Here's a copy of Player.log in the hopes that somebody smarter than me can tell me what's going on:
